@cnuernber What I mean by the private header is not about moving them to cc file, but instead put it under src/contrib/cblas/gemm_common.h, then you can include the header by using a relative path to the file. 

There are other examples of private headers, e.g. https://github.com/dmlc/tvm/blob/master/src/contrib/cudnn/cudnn_utils.h

The general idea is that these headers can be used by TVM internally, but we do not intend to expose it to the users of TVM

